\end{align*}

collapse.paragraphs:
 Row-reduce $A$ to form a row-equivalent matrix in reduced row-echelon form,
\begin{align*}
\displaystyle B=\begin{bmatrix}\boxed{1}&0&0&2&-1\\
0&\boxed{1}&0&3&1\\
0&0&\boxed{1}&-2&5\\
0&0&0&0&0\end{bmatrix}
\end{align*}

